name: ConditionalFormatDataBarFormat
description: Represents a conditional format DataBar Format for the positive or negative side of the data bar.

properties.name: color
properties.description: HTML color code representing the color of the border line, of the form #RRGGBB (e.g. "FFA500") or as a named HTML color (e.g. "orange").

properties.name: gradient
properties.description: Boolean representation of whether or not the DataBar has a gradient.

properties.name: borderColor
properties.description: HTML color code representing the color of the border line, of the form #RRGGBB (e.g. "FFA500") or as a named HTML color (e.g. "orange").

methods.name: load
methods.description: Fills the proxy object created in JavaScript layer with property and object values specified in the parameter.

parameters.name: param
parameters.description: Accepts parameter and relationship names as delimited string or an array. Or, provide [loadOption](loadoption.md) object.
